NNOOTTEESS
       The output site list will have the easting and northing  of  the  input
       site  list.  The category value will either be the same as the value in
       the input site list or a unique value if there were  no  categories  in
       the  input  site list.  One decimal attribute will be output containing
       either, the cell value of the raster if no comparison  was  done  (i.e.
       aattttrr==nnoonnee)  or it will be the difference between the cell value and the
       site list attribute value.


       If --ll is specified, it is important that the raster category  label  is
       numeric.  No  error  checking  is  done  except for "no data" values as
       raster category labels. In this instance, a warning  is  issued  and  a
       zero value is assumed.


       When  NULL  values  are  encountered  for  a  cell,  zero value is used
       instead.  In these cases, more acurrate  results  may  be  obtained  by
       using the default nearest neighbor comparisons.


       This  program  may  not  work  properly with lat-long data when the --BBCC
       flags are used.


       When interpolation is done (i.e., the --BBCC flags are used),  values  are
       assumed  to  be located at the centroid of grid cells.  Therefore, cur-
       rent resolution settings are important.

